			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Job Description: </strong>MashON is looking for a Production Intern to help bolster our awesome merchandise team. You will help with the web production work for the assets, backgrounds, and other elements needed for our apps and admin system. Ideally you are someone who is comfortable working in Photoshop, Illustrator, and Indesign, and can easily create and convert designs into the elements we need. You&rsquo;ll need to be able to quickly take existing photographs and images and composite them into new images. You will become very familiar with our admin system (which is the repository and heart of our applications) and learn all the in&rsquo;s and out&rsquo;s. You will also be instrumental in helping create and complie documentation, as well as helping to create manageable ways for the Merchandise team to access and organize different aspects of our products offering. You should also have great attention to detail, as you will be working with spreadsheets and other documents, putting these into our admin system.</p>
<p>
Reports to: Merchandise Manager / Manager, Product Development</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Core Responsibilities:</strong><br />
1. Convert designs into production elements (web graphics, hex color values, etc)<br />
2. Take existing product images and assets and prepare/composite said images into templates ready for use in our platform.<br />
3. Creating new products and managing existing products in our admin system, which includes gathering product information from spreadsheets and uploading into the admin system.<br />
4. Create graphics for website and mobile graphic production<br />
5. Template standardization<br />
6. Prepare design assets<br />
7. Produce digital assets from established art direction</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Required Experience &amp; Knowledge:</strong><br />
1. Currently enrolled in a program (or have graduated from a program) relating to fine arts, graphic design or other related discipline<br />
2. Passion for the digital realm, with a good sense of where things are headed<br />
3. Good sense of core design methodologies<br />
4. Must be proficient in Adobe Creative Suite and MS Office<br />
5. Knowledge of HTML, CSS and other web technologies a plus<br />
6. Photography and knowledge of prepping for traditional print a plus<br />
7. Good verbal, written, and organizational skills<br />
8. Good teamwork and cross departmental communication skills<br />
9. Good time management, attention to detail, and a willingness to be a team player</p>
